WEBVTT

00:07.398 --> 00:09.792
- Here. I know you have
your chemistry test today,

00:09.879 --> 00:12.447
and I know you're gonna ace it,
as you always do.

00:12.534 --> 00:14.231
- I won't if I eat all that.

00:16.016 --> 00:18.714
But this looks too good
to pass up.

00:18.801 --> 00:20.194
Thanks, Mom.

00:20.281 --> 00:22.239
And I hope you crush
your work presentation.

00:22.326 --> 00:23.458
[knocking on door]

00:23.545 --> 00:24.981
- If that is Mr. Cross

00:25.068 --> 00:26.548
complaining about
the trees again--

00:26.635 --> 00:28.637
- He's just lonely, Mom.
- Yeah.

00:28.724 --> 00:30.813
That's the most dangerous
kind of man.

00:36.079 --> 00:37.211
Noah, you can't be here.

00:37.298 --> 00:39.039
- No, I-I just
wanna talk to her.

00:40.779 --> 00:41.824
Ruthie!

00:41.911 --> 00:43.608
Hey, it's--it's me, Noah.

00:43.695 --> 00:45.654
- Ruthie, get back
in the kitchen.

00:45.741 --> 00:47.351
- Mom. Mom--

00:47.438 --> 00:50.050
- You text her again,
and I am calling the cops.

00:50.137 --> 00:52.226
- Please, Mom, I-I just wanna
see what she remembers.

00:52.313 --> 00:54.184
- Nothing. And we're going to
keep it that way.

00:54.271 --> 00:55.838
- I've been working
on myself, all right?

00:55.925 --> 00:57.753
These family secrets, they
only have power over you

00:57.840 --> 00:59.102
when you keep them in the dark.

00:59.189 --> 01:01.974
- You're not a part
of our family.

01:02.062 --> 01:04.412
You are a monster,
and you cannot be fixed.

01:09.765 --> 01:12.115
Now go, and don't
ever come back.

01:12.202 --> 01:13.856
- Mom.

01:13.943 --> 01:16.641
[somber music]

01:16.728 --> 01:20.558
♪ ♪

01:20.645 --> 01:23.561
- Did you ever think a book
about generational trauma

01:23.648 --> 01:24.649
would land you on
the bestsellers list

01:24.736 --> 01:25.998
for six months?

01:26.086 --> 01:28.523
- If my book has helped
even one person

01:28.610 --> 01:29.915
struggling with family trauma

01:30.002 --> 01:31.395
passed down
through generations,

01:31.482 --> 01:33.005
then I've done my job.

01:33.093 --> 01:34.398
- That's Olivia Kramer,

01:34.485 --> 01:36.052
world-renowned
child psychiatrist,

01:36.139 --> 01:37.967
whose book is in stores now.

01:38.054 --> 01:39.795
Thank you, Doctor.

01:39.882 --> 01:42.319
- Thank you.
Always a pleasure.

01:48.804 --> 01:49.979
[gasps]
- Oh, sorry.

01:50.066 --> 01:51.720
I didn't mean to scare you.

01:51.807 --> 01:53.243
- No.
I don't see walk-ins,

01:53.330 --> 01:54.723
except for my current patients
who are in crisis.

01:54.810 --> 01:56.246
- No, I'm not a walk-in.

01:56.333 --> 01:58.422
You already know me.

01:58.509 --> 02:00.642
Well, you know my
half-sister, Ruthie Denham,

02:00.729 --> 02:02.818
from ten years ago.

02:02.905 --> 02:05.125
- You're Noah.

02:07.475 --> 02:09.651
- Wait--so she--
so she told you my name?

02:09.738 --> 02:12.393
What else did she say about me?

02:12.480 --> 02:13.785
- I can't discuss
that with you, Noah.

02:13.872 --> 02:15.657
It's confidential.

02:15.744 --> 02:17.180
You'll need to leave.

02:17.267 --> 02:18.964
- Why the hell won't
anyone talk to me, huh?

02:19.051 --> 02:21.141
About me!

02:23.578 --> 02:25.754
What are you doing?
- I'm calling security.

02:25.841 --> 02:27.712
- Put that away.
I said, put that away!

02:27.799 --> 02:30.976
[dark music]

02:31.063 --> 02:33.370
I need to know
if I'm a monster,

02:33.457 --> 02:36.547
and you're gonna
help me find out.

02:36.634 --> 02:38.462
- Okay.

02:38.549 --> 02:41.204
You don't want to do this.
- Move. Move.

02:41.291 --> 02:44.033
[tense music]

02:47.993 --> 02:49.778
- I can't believe
you read my texts.

02:49.865 --> 02:51.171
- What made you feel like
you had to lie to me?

02:51.258 --> 02:52.781
- I didn't!
- Ingrid.

02:52.868 --> 02:55.175
You said you were going
to Samantha's, right, tonight?

02:55.262 --> 02:57.046
You did not say you were going
upstate to some college party

02:57.133 --> 02:58.352
to do God knows what
with God knows who.

02:58.439 --> 03:01.311
- It's my friends.
It's not a big deal.

03:01.398 --> 03:03.095
- You know what?
It is a big deal.

03:03.183 --> 03:04.532
And had you told me the truth,
it might have been different.

03:04.619 --> 03:06.316
Let me ask you, how am I
supposed to trust you

03:06.403 --> 03:09.624
when you hide things from me?
- Yeah, you're one to talk.

03:09.711 --> 03:10.929
- I'm sorry?

03:11.016 --> 03:13.236
- You hide things
from me all the time.

03:13.323 --> 03:14.629
You leave.
Sometimes you're gone for days.

03:14.716 --> 03:16.065
And then you come back,

03:16.152 --> 03:17.327
and you don't tell me
anything about it.

03:17.414 --> 03:19.547
- That is different,
and you know it.

03:19.634 --> 03:21.375
It's my work, and I'm an adult.

03:21.462 --> 03:24.334
- So am I! I'm 18 now.
- You are 18

03:24.421 --> 03:26.075
and still in high school
and still living in my house.

03:26.162 --> 03:27.685
And therefore, still my rules.
You're not going.

03:27.772 --> 03:29.426
It's not happening.
- But--

03:30.775 --> 03:32.995
[groans]

03:33.082 --> 03:35.040
Mom, please.
[phone buzzes]

03:35.127 --> 03:36.477
- It's work.
I have to go.

03:36.564 --> 03:37.608
- [mocking] It's work.
I gotta go.

03:41.221 --> 03:42.439
- You know what?

03:42.526 --> 03:44.528
You're staying at
your father's tonight.

03:44.615 --> 03:46.878
I'll be calling to check in.

03:48.358 --> 03:50.882
- Ugh!

03:50.969 --> 03:53.494
- Approximately 90 minutes ago,

03:53.581 --> 03:55.147
an unknown subject
entered the office

03:55.235 --> 03:57.324
of Dr. Olivia Kramer
and forcefully abducted her.

03:57.411 --> 03:59.674
Dr. Kramer had just concluded
a live Zoom interview

03:59.761 --> 04:01.415
with a local morning show.

04:01.502 --> 04:03.852
She turned off her camera
but not her audio.

04:03.939 --> 04:05.636
Producers heard the abduction
taking place in real time

04:05.723 --> 04:07.638
and called 911.

04:07.725 --> 04:09.205
- Has there been
a ransom demand?

04:09.292 --> 04:10.598
- Not at this time.

04:10.685 --> 04:12.556
- Thought she was a celebrity,
not a saint.

04:12.643 --> 04:15.298
- I'd say she's considered
a bit of both.

04:15.385 --> 04:17.213
She's helped
a lot of people deal with

04:17.300 --> 04:20.042
the effects of sexual abuse
and generational trauma.

04:20.129 --> 04:22.131
- Abusers begetting abusers.

04:22.218 --> 04:23.437
- Right.

04:23.524 --> 04:25.917
She's also an expert
at diagnosing

04:26.004 --> 04:27.789
accommodation syndrome
in adults.

04:27.876 --> 04:29.443
- I take it
you've read the books.

04:29.530 --> 04:31.662
- Yeah. All three.

04:31.749 --> 04:33.273
- Why?

04:33.360 --> 04:34.883
- Hey, Ray, can you
check out the garage

04:34.970 --> 04:36.667
for Dr. Kramer's black Audi?

04:36.754 --> 04:37.886
- Yeah.
- Thanks.

04:42.064 --> 04:44.240
- You didn't have to do that.

04:44.327 --> 04:46.503
- Does he know what happened
to you on that boat

04:46.590 --> 04:49.332
when you were undercover?

04:49.419 --> 04:50.855
- No.

04:50.942 --> 04:53.075
It's not exactly, um...

04:53.162 --> 04:55.295
day-to-day conversation,
you know?

04:56.600 --> 04:58.602
- If you ever wanna
talk about it--

04:58.689 --> 05:01.301
taking down Oscar Zamora,
or anything else--

05:01.388 --> 05:03.041
I'm here.

05:03.128 --> 05:05.827
Just trying to respect
your boundaries.

05:07.611 --> 05:09.091
- Thank you.

05:15.097 --> 05:17.186
- Audio from the Zoom cued up?
- Yeah.

05:17.273 --> 05:19.536
First part's too garbled to
make out, but listen to this.

05:19.623 --> 05:21.146
- I need to know
if I'm a monster,

05:21.233 --> 05:22.713
and you're gonna
help me find out.

05:22.800 --> 05:25.716
- Our unsub's a male,
and he sounds young.

05:25.803 --> 05:27.283
- I think we can rule
out a ransom demand.

05:27.370 --> 05:28.415
"I need to know
if I'm a monster,

05:28.502 --> 05:29.633
and you're going
help me find out?"

05:29.720 --> 05:31.200
That's a--
that's a call for help.

05:31.287 --> 05:32.941
- You think
it's an old patient?

05:33.028 --> 05:34.899
- He chose to come to her.

05:34.986 --> 05:36.945
He could have wound up on
any therapist's doorstep.

05:37.032 --> 05:38.990
- True, but given what you said
about her expertise,

05:39.077 --> 05:41.079
the doc's also heard
the names of lots of

05:41.166 --> 05:42.646
sexual predators
inside these walls.

05:42.733 --> 05:44.431
- She'd be
a mandatory reporter.

05:44.518 --> 05:47.303
Our unsub could be
angry at being unmasked.

05:47.390 --> 05:49.653
- Dr. Kramer's Audi
wasn't in the garage.

05:49.740 --> 05:51.438
I already put a BOLO out.

05:51.525 --> 05:54.919
- Well, who needs people when
you have surveillance footage?

05:55.006 --> 05:56.965
Oh, look. The violent man
is dragging the woman

05:57.052 --> 05:58.967
into the concrete dungeon.

05:59.054 --> 06:01.273
Why does it feel like we've
seen this movie too many times?

06:01.361 --> 06:03.928
- We got you out.
We'll get her, too.

06:04.015 --> 06:05.277
I'm gonna save my breath,
because I already know

06:05.365 --> 06:06.496
you ran the facial rec,

06:06.583 --> 06:08.106
and skip to
the burning question.

06:08.193 --> 06:09.804
What's this
sicko-with-a-gun's name?

06:09.891 --> 06:11.196
- Noah Tramble, 25.

06:11.283 --> 06:12.415
Record of possession.

06:12.502 --> 06:15.549
His last known
is in Hagerstown.

06:15.636 --> 06:17.768
His next of kin is his father,
Casper, who's currently a guest

06:17.855 --> 06:19.335
of the Maryland
Department of Corrections

06:19.422 --> 06:21.163
for sexual abuse of a child.

06:21.250 --> 06:23.295
- [sighs] Get Noah Tramble's
photo on the wire.

06:23.383 --> 06:26.473
I want her patient files.
Line up the grudges.

06:26.560 --> 06:28.692
You two take Noah's
last known in Hagerstown.

06:28.779 --> 06:29.824
Ray, you're with me.
- Where we going?

06:29.911 --> 06:32.522
- Prison.

06:33.915 --> 06:35.612
- I told you,

06:35.699 --> 06:36.874
it's doctor-patient
confidentiality.

06:36.961 --> 06:39.007
- I don't care.
Waive it.

06:39.094 --> 06:41.052
What did Ruthie
say I did to her?

06:41.139 --> 06:43.446
- What do you think you did?

06:43.533 --> 06:45.230
- No, no, no, no, no.
Don't redirect the question.

06:45.317 --> 06:47.276
I know all your shrink tricks.

06:47.363 --> 06:48.669
Now, I've been
journaling lately,

06:48.756 --> 06:50.235
trying to work things out.

06:50.322 --> 06:52.673
- Then why do you need me?

06:52.760 --> 06:56.459
- Lady, I wouldn't be
asking that if I were you.

07:04.989 --> 07:07.339
- If you want my help,

07:07.427 --> 07:09.646
you're going to
have to tell the truth.

07:11.648 --> 07:13.258
Can you do that, Noah?

07:18.089 --> 07:19.526
What do you think
you did to Ruthie?

07:19.613 --> 07:20.875
- I don't know.

07:20.962 --> 07:23.181
I was drinking a lot
back then, you know?

07:23.268 --> 07:25.096
Snorting anything
I could get my hands on.

07:25.183 --> 07:26.010
Adderall, coke, oxy.

07:26.097 --> 07:28.796
- You were 15.

07:28.883 --> 07:30.014
You must have had
some reason for going down

07:30.101 --> 07:31.668
such a dark path.

07:31.755 --> 07:33.148
- Well, I--

07:37.152 --> 07:38.849
I didn't wanna exist.
I--

07:40.547 --> 07:41.678
[crying softly]

07:41.765 --> 07:43.463
- I know how difficult
that was to say.

07:45.987 --> 07:48.555
And...I want to tell you

07:48.642 --> 07:50.470
what I remember your sister
saying about you--

07:52.646 --> 07:56.432
That she loved her
brother very much.

07:59.479 --> 08:01.263
- She's my half-sister.

08:02.786 --> 08:04.571
We've got different fathers,
I mean...

08:04.658 --> 08:05.876
hers is a lawyer.

08:05.963 --> 08:07.487
Mine's a piece of crap.

08:07.574 --> 08:08.705
- I'm sorry.

08:08.792 --> 08:11.447
No child deserves that.

08:13.318 --> 08:17.627
Can you tell me why you think
you might have hurt Ruthie?

08:17.714 --> 08:19.716
- Because that's
what everybody said!

08:19.803 --> 08:21.370
Because of my
biological father.

08:21.457 --> 08:23.328
- Tell me about him.

08:23.415 --> 08:26.114
- No, he--look, he--
- Noah.

08:26.201 --> 08:27.507
[no sound]

08:30.858 --> 08:33.121
- Maryland state troopers
have advised residents

08:33.208 --> 08:34.426
to be on the lookout

08:34.514 --> 08:36.167
for this man, Noah Tramble,

08:36.254 --> 08:37.821
wanted for the abduction of...

08:37.908 --> 08:40.476
- Noah, tell me about
your father.

08:40.563 --> 08:42.260
- No, no. Not here.
- Did he do something to you?

08:42.347 --> 08:44.219
- I said not here, all right?

08:44.306 --> 08:46.003
-...should not be approached
under any circumstances.

08:46.090 --> 08:48.092
- All right, let's go.
- Noah.

08:48.179 --> 08:50.355
- Thank you.

08:50.442 --> 08:52.706
Hana says there's no record
of Noah Tramble

08:52.793 --> 08:54.142
being one of Dr. Kramer's
patients.

08:54.229 --> 08:56.492
- Kristin said his place
is empty,

08:56.579 --> 08:58.973
except for a few end tables
and some clothes.

08:59.060 --> 09:01.105
Neighbors haven't seen him
in a couple of days, either.

09:03.673 --> 09:05.153
[quietly] Get ready to meet
the devil himself.

09:13.030 --> 09:14.336
- Hey!

09:16.033 --> 09:18.558
- Mr. Tramble.

09:18.645 --> 09:20.081
We figured we'd give you
the courtesy

09:20.168 --> 09:21.865
of bringing you down
to the infirmary

09:21.952 --> 09:22.953
so your colleagues
wouldn't label you as a snitch.

09:23.040 --> 09:24.607
- Ha.

09:24.694 --> 09:28.176
- I know it's hard enough
being a pedo in gen pop.

09:28.263 --> 09:30.918
- Where'd you find this kid?
He's a real catch.

09:31.005 --> 09:33.181
- Yeah, the best and brightest.

09:33.268 --> 09:34.835
That's why I hired him.

09:34.922 --> 09:37.228
Have you heard from
your son recently?

09:37.315 --> 09:40.623
- Can't say
till I get my potato chips.

09:40.710 --> 09:42.364
- You know, I waited
so long for you that I--

09:42.451 --> 09:44.192
I just had to open the bag.

09:44.279 --> 09:47.238
Mmm!
So delicious.

09:47.325 --> 09:50.807
You know, if you give us
some useful information,

09:50.894 --> 09:54.332
I might be able to
dig you up a bag.

09:54.419 --> 09:55.812
- Noah stopped talking to me

09:55.899 --> 09:57.814
after I landed in here
two years back.

09:57.901 --> 09:59.860
- But he was in your custody
from the time he was 15

09:59.947 --> 10:01.035
till he graduated high school.

10:01.122 --> 10:02.602
Why not before?

10:02.689 --> 10:04.647
- 'Cause my ex,
Noah's mother Sandy,

10:04.734 --> 10:07.084
got all pissed off when
she came home from work

10:07.171 --> 10:11.306
and caught me with a lady
who wasn't age appropriate.

10:11.393 --> 10:14.048
That's not the best part.

10:14.135 --> 10:16.616
Sandy files for divorce
when Noah's around seven,

10:16.703 --> 10:18.226
and who does she remarry?

10:18.313 --> 10:21.751
Her attorney, Luke Denham.

10:21.838 --> 10:25.233
The one who bled me dry of
the nothing I never had.

10:25.320 --> 10:26.495
Polished prick.

10:26.582 --> 10:29.629
He took in Noah as his own,

10:29.716 --> 10:32.544
had a daughter
two years later.

10:32.632 --> 10:35.112
One big happy family.

10:35.199 --> 10:36.505
Pricks.

10:36.592 --> 10:38.594
- How did Noah end up
back with you?

10:38.681 --> 10:41.031
- Kid was a druggie.
I think he was hooked on oxy.

10:41.118 --> 10:42.598
Luke and Sandy
threw him back at me

10:42.685 --> 10:44.121
like he was a piece of trash.

10:44.208 --> 10:45.688
- You ever hurt Noah?

10:47.559 --> 10:49.300
- My son was never my type.

10:51.433 --> 10:53.391
- I need a shower.

10:53.478 --> 10:56.351
Casper could be the reason
Noah thinks he's a monster.

10:56.438 --> 10:58.483
Because his father is.

10:58.570 --> 11:01.051
- Well, Noah moved out of his
father's house when he was 18.

11:01.138 --> 11:03.097
Casper didn't get charged
with a sexual offense

11:03.184 --> 11:04.489
until two years ago.

11:04.576 --> 11:05.795
- Just because
he wasn't convicted

11:05.882 --> 11:07.231
doesn't mean
he's not a predator.

11:07.318 --> 11:09.059
Could be an open
secret in the family.

11:09.146 --> 11:11.279
Which makes it unresolved
generational trauma,

11:11.366 --> 11:13.063
the doc's specialty.

11:13.150 --> 11:15.326
- Yeah, but Noah's not
Dr. Kramer's patient.

11:15.413 --> 11:16.893
All right, why abduct her
to help him?

11:16.980 --> 11:18.590
- I don't know.

11:24.292 --> 11:26.424
Hana, is there any record
of a patient

11:26.511 --> 11:29.819
with the last name Denham
in Dr. Kramer's files?

11:33.562 --> 11:35.216
- One, from a decade ago.

11:35.303 --> 11:38.045
Ruthie Denham, age five.

11:38.132 --> 11:40.482
Same childhood address as Noah.

11:40.569 --> 11:41.918
Because she's his half-sister.

11:42.005 --> 11:44.573
- Send Gaines
and Barnes over now.

11:48.403 --> 11:51.754
[edgy music]

11:51.841 --> 11:54.017
♪ ♪

11:54.104 --> 11:56.063
- FBI.
Anybody home?

11:58.892 --> 11:59.936
- It's open.

12:05.986 --> 12:07.944
- Oh my God.

12:08.858 --> 12:10.947
She's alive.
Throw me that towel.

12:11.034 --> 12:12.079
- Here.

12:12.166 --> 12:13.776
- Hey.
- We need an ambulance.

12:13.863 --> 12:15.299
- Ruthie, stay with me.
- 81 Regent Avenue, Hagerstown.

12:15.386 --> 12:17.780
- Take that.

12:17.867 --> 12:19.303
Stay with me.
- You're gonna be all right.

12:19.390 --> 12:20.870
- Come on, come on.

12:20.957 --> 12:23.307
- Can you hear me?
- Keep breathing.

12:23.394 --> 12:25.396
Ruthie, keep breathing.

12:31.838 --> 12:33.535
[distant siren]

12:33.622 --> 12:35.145
- How's she doing?

12:35.232 --> 12:36.799
- Lost a lot of blood,
but she's stable.

12:36.886 --> 12:38.801
They've got her sedated.
- Her parents here?

12:38.888 --> 12:40.542
- Luke and Sandy.
They're divorced.

12:40.629 --> 12:41.848
Sandy's inside
with the doctors,

12:41.935 --> 12:43.414
completely beside herself.

12:43.501 --> 12:45.373
- Well, her daughter
tried to kill herself,

12:45.460 --> 12:46.983
and her son's
a wanted fugitive.

12:47.070 --> 12:48.680
Can't say I blame her.

12:48.768 --> 12:50.073
Noah found Dr. Kramer

12:50.160 --> 12:51.596
because Ruthie was a patient
a decade ago.

12:51.683 --> 12:53.424
We need to find out who
gave him that information.

12:53.511 --> 12:55.209
- I'm looking for my
daughter, Ruthie Denham.

12:55.296 --> 12:57.559
- Check with the front desk.
- You must be her father, Luke.

12:57.646 --> 12:59.256
- Yes. They told me that
they brought her here.

12:59.343 --> 13:00.780
Is-is she okay?
- She's stable.

13:00.867 --> 13:02.129
The doctors are taking
good care of her.

13:02.216 --> 13:04.087
Her mom's already here.

13:04.174 --> 13:06.089
- Did Ruthie really
slit her wrist?

13:06.176 --> 13:08.178
Why would she do that?
- We don't know.

13:08.265 --> 13:09.701
But we'd like to talk
to you and her mom,

13:09.789 --> 13:12.269
after you've had
a chance to see her.

13:12.356 --> 13:14.750
- This is Noah's fault.
It has to be.

13:14.837 --> 13:15.795
- Why do you say that?

13:15.882 --> 13:17.579
- Because he's a bad seed.

13:17.666 --> 13:19.102
Always has been.

13:24.238 --> 13:26.283
- Where are we going?

13:26.370 --> 13:28.111
My car is the other way.
- Forget your car.

13:28.198 --> 13:29.591
The cops are
looking for it now.

13:29.678 --> 13:31.375
- I have to
tell you something.

13:31.462 --> 13:34.117
There's a chance you may never
know the truth about yourself.

13:34.204 --> 13:35.205
- What kind of monster
doesn't remember

13:35.292 --> 13:36.250
whether or not
he molested his own sister?

13:36.337 --> 13:38.208
- It was a decade ago.

13:38.295 --> 13:40.732
You were abusing drugs, and
memories in the best of times

13:40.820 --> 13:42.343
are complex.

13:42.430 --> 13:44.432
If enough people told you
that you hurt your sister,

13:44.519 --> 13:46.129
you might have
begun to believe it.

13:46.216 --> 13:47.609
- You mean I might
not have done it?

13:47.696 --> 13:51.091
- Yes. Yes, and I can help you,
if you let me.

13:51.178 --> 13:52.832
Why are you doing this?
- For Rose.

13:52.919 --> 13:56.052
It's always been for her.
- Who's Rose?

13:56.139 --> 13:58.359
- You're gonna see.
Get in.

13:58.446 --> 13:59.577
Get in!

14:04.931 --> 14:07.847
[tense music]

14:07.934 --> 14:12.460
♪ ♪

14:12.547 --> 14:14.331
- Hey! Hey!

14:14.418 --> 14:16.246
What the hell
you think you're doing?

14:16.333 --> 14:18.248
- Hey--
- You come here

14:18.335 --> 14:19.336
and steal my truck?
- Relax, man--uhh--

14:19.423 --> 14:20.598
[grunting]

14:27.736 --> 14:30.565
- Hey! Stay there!

14:30.652 --> 14:31.653
[labored breathing]

14:31.740 --> 14:32.784
It was self-defense.

14:32.872 --> 14:33.960
He was going to kill me.

14:34.047 --> 14:36.440
Get back in the truck.

14:36.527 --> 14:38.007
Get back
in the truck!

14:43.752 --> 14:45.754
- Noah, we can't
just leave him.

14:45.841 --> 14:47.364
- We got to go.

14:52.630 --> 14:54.371
- Oh my God.

14:57.853 --> 14:59.637
- Do we really have
to do this right now?

14:59.724 --> 15:01.770
- I know this is hard, but
this is an active abduction

15:01.857 --> 15:03.293
and we need to know.

15:03.380 --> 15:04.904
Can you tell us when the
last time was you saw Noah?

15:04.991 --> 15:06.122
- This morning.

15:06.209 --> 15:07.080
He came to the house
to see Ruthie,

15:07.167 --> 15:08.472
but I wouldn't let him in.

15:08.559 --> 15:10.692
- Do Noah and Ruthie
see each other often?

15:10.779 --> 15:12.215
- Never.

15:12.302 --> 15:13.695
No, not for a decade.

15:13.782 --> 15:15.305
The last communication
they had was...

15:15.392 --> 15:17.177
yesterday, when he texted her.

15:17.264 --> 15:18.830
But I put a stop to that.

15:18.918 --> 15:19.919
- Why?

15:23.400 --> 15:26.926
- Be-because of
what he did to her.

15:29.537 --> 15:31.017
- What happened?

15:31.104 --> 15:32.844
- [sighs]

15:32.932 --> 15:35.282
It was March 1, 2013.

15:35.369 --> 15:37.284
I went to wake Ruthie up
for kindergarten.

15:37.371 --> 15:39.808
She was asleep in her
little sleigh bed,

15:39.895 --> 15:43.029
with Noah spooning her.

15:43.116 --> 15:46.510
He'd never done that before,
and I thought it was cute.

15:46.597 --> 15:49.513
But then I woke them up,
and I pulled back the covers.

15:50.862 --> 15:53.909
And they were both naked.

15:53.996 --> 15:56.433
I just--I just lost it.

15:58.609 --> 16:01.830
I asked Noah if he--you know,
if he touched her.

16:01.917 --> 16:04.180
And he just started crying.
He said he couldn't remember.

16:04.267 --> 16:04.876
He said he didn't
even know what

16:04.964 --> 16:06.530
he was doing in Ruthie's bed.

16:06.617 --> 16:08.532
But I could smell
the booze on his breath.

16:08.619 --> 16:11.622
He was drunk,
and probably high.

16:11.709 --> 16:13.581
Oh God, he was on
so many drugs back then.

16:15.104 --> 16:16.976
- What did Ruthie say happened?

16:17.063 --> 16:18.629
- She was five.

16:18.716 --> 16:20.805
She was scared,
and he was screaming.

16:20.892 --> 16:22.198
And I was, too.

16:22.285 --> 16:24.026
And she thought that
I was mad at her.

16:24.113 --> 16:26.724
- And where was your husband?

16:26.811 --> 16:28.335
- Luke was in trial
in Baltimore.

16:28.422 --> 16:29.858
But he came as
soon as I told him.

16:29.945 --> 16:31.207
- Did you call the police?

16:34.297 --> 16:35.733
- I wanted to,

16:35.820 --> 16:38.258
but Luke
talked me out of it.

16:38.345 --> 16:39.520
I was so angry--
I would do anything

16:39.607 --> 16:41.565
to protect my daughter.

16:41.652 --> 16:43.176
- And yet, Noah was your son.

16:44.612 --> 16:46.483
- I loved him so much.

16:46.570 --> 16:48.529
But how could he do
that to his own sister?

16:49.791 --> 16:51.706
- I'm sorry.

16:51.793 --> 16:54.404
- I didn't want to believe it,
but he was so ashamed.

16:54.491 --> 16:56.972
Noah never stopped
crying all day.

16:57.059 --> 16:59.670
And the more that he said
he couldn't remember,

16:59.757 --> 17:00.932
the more I knew
that he had done it,

17:01.020 --> 17:02.891
and I could not forgive him.

17:02.978 --> 17:04.849
- Noah was an addict.

17:04.936 --> 17:07.722
Oxy, meth, coke.

17:07.809 --> 17:09.680
The kind that make you
wreak havoc.

17:09.767 --> 17:11.247
- You're speaking
from experience?

17:11.334 --> 17:12.901
- I'm a family law attorney.

17:12.988 --> 17:14.511
I've seen what substance
abuse can do

17:14.598 --> 17:17.732
to every kind of family,
including mine.

17:17.819 --> 17:21.692
- So you think the drugs
made Noah molest his sister?

17:21.779 --> 17:24.869
- It's completely within
the realm of possibility.

17:24.956 --> 17:28.656
Ruthie was too young to have
the words to be sure, so...

17:28.743 --> 17:30.571
even after she went
to see Dr. Kramer,

17:30.658 --> 17:32.921
she still referred to it
as "the nightmare."

17:33.008 --> 17:36.751
- I have to ask--
where were you that night?

17:36.838 --> 17:40.146
- I was in trial in Baltimore.

17:40.233 --> 17:42.670
Hadn't been home all week
until Sandy called.

17:42.757 --> 17:44.976
- We'll have to confirm that.

17:45.064 --> 17:46.978
- Well, you go right ahead.

17:47.066 --> 17:48.415
I love my daughter.

17:48.502 --> 17:50.765
I would never do
anything to hurt her.

17:50.852 --> 17:52.767
- You know, I'm curious
about something, Mr. Denham.

17:52.854 --> 17:56.292
Sandy said that you talked
her out of calling the police.

17:57.772 --> 17:59.774
Why was that?

18:04.083 --> 18:06.476
- Noah was only 15.

18:06.563 --> 18:09.740
At minimum, he'd be
stigmatized for life,

18:09.827 --> 18:11.916
and more likely thrown in jail.

18:12.003 --> 18:13.657
Given the circumstances,

18:13.744 --> 18:16.530
it just didn't seem like the
right thing to do at the time.

18:16.617 --> 18:20.055
You don't think I regret
that decision every day?

18:20.142 --> 18:21.709
I tried to help Noah.

18:23.014 --> 18:25.756
It broke my marriage, it broke
my daughter, and it broke me.

18:25.843 --> 18:28.411
We should have turned him in
when we had the chance.

18:28.498 --> 18:29.456
- [clears throat]

18:31.284 --> 18:32.546
- Thank you.

18:34.678 --> 18:36.550
- Ruthie's cell phone.

18:36.637 --> 18:37.942
Noah's been texting her
the past few days.

18:38.029 --> 18:39.640
She didn't respond
until this morning,

18:39.727 --> 18:42.425
after he'd gone to
the house to see her.

18:42.512 --> 18:44.166
- "I don't remember
what happened.

18:44.253 --> 18:45.907
Maybe Dr. Kramer knows."

18:45.994 --> 18:48.127
- That's how Noah
found the doctor.

18:48.214 --> 18:49.519
[phone rings]
- Well, if Ruth blames herself,

18:49.606 --> 18:51.086
that explains her suicide
attempt.

18:51.173 --> 18:52.696
- Hey.

18:52.783 --> 18:54.524
- Remy, Clarksburg PD
found Dr. Kramer's Audi

18:54.611 --> 18:56.352
parked at a hotel,
three blocks from

18:56.439 --> 18:59.703
the side street where Noah
killed a man for his truck.

19:01.836 --> 19:03.490
- Victim is George Mason.
Works around the corner.

19:03.577 --> 19:04.752
Parks his truck
back here sometimes,

19:04.839 --> 19:06.623
when the employee lot's full.

19:06.710 --> 19:07.972
- Is she our witness?
- Yeah.

19:08.059 --> 19:10.018
Said she saw Mason
catch a fugitive

19:10.105 --> 19:11.976
trying to steal his truck.
Pulled that tire iron on him,

19:12.063 --> 19:13.413
and your guy
shot him twice in the gut.

19:13.500 --> 19:14.805
- His name's Noah Tramble.

19:14.892 --> 19:16.633
She see his hostage?
- Yeah. Black female,

19:16.720 --> 19:18.287
dressed nice, sitting in
the cab of the truck.

19:18.374 --> 19:19.593
- Well, at least she's alive.

19:19.680 --> 19:21.595
At least we got that.

19:23.684 --> 19:25.076
- Oh, he's escalating.

19:25.164 --> 19:26.513
You got the info on the truck?

19:26.600 --> 19:27.992
- Yeah, I was about
to run it in my car.

19:28.079 --> 19:29.516
- All right.

19:29.603 --> 19:30.169
Why don't you take that,
handle the BOLO.

19:30.256 --> 19:31.344
I'll go talk to the witness.

19:31.431 --> 19:32.649
We'll meet up after
and canvass.

19:34.477 --> 19:37.915
[uneasy music]

19:38.002 --> 19:44.487
♪ ♪

19:53.017 --> 19:55.019
- You can have vegetables.
- I don't want vegetables.

19:55.106 --> 19:58.632
- That's Rose
and her daughter Chloe.

19:58.719 --> 19:59.807
- I don't wanna go home.

19:59.894 --> 20:02.679
- How old's Chloe?
- She's five.

20:02.766 --> 20:03.898
- That's the same age
Ruthie was--

20:03.985 --> 20:05.247
- Don't go there.

20:05.334 --> 20:07.249
You're on my team now.

20:07.336 --> 20:09.295
You said you would help me.

20:13.473 --> 20:16.780
She's gonna take me back.

20:16.867 --> 20:19.174
She knows the worst
thing I might have done.

20:19.261 --> 20:22.482
And she's gonna say
I love you anyways.

20:22.569 --> 20:24.266
You're gonna help me, right?

20:31.665 --> 20:33.754
- Hi. I-I just got home
from work, and I--

20:33.841 --> 20:37.279
I turned on the news, and
I saw my--my ex-boyfriend.

20:37.366 --> 20:38.454
Noah Tramble.

20:38.541 --> 20:39.455
I just kicked him
out yesterday.

20:39.542 --> 20:40.935
[knocking on door]

20:41.022 --> 20:43.024
- Rose?

20:43.111 --> 20:44.765
- [whispering] Oh, God.
- It's me.

20:44.852 --> 20:47.289
- He's here. He's here.
Call the police, now!

20:47.376 --> 20:49.204
Honey, go upstairs, all right?
- Come on, I know

20:49.291 --> 20:50.684
you're in there.
- Yeah, take that.

20:50.771 --> 20:52.381
Go really fast.
I love you so much, okay?

20:52.468 --> 20:53.556
[knocking continues]

20:53.643 --> 20:55.950
[breathing heavily]

20:56.037 --> 20:59.823
- No, it's okay, it's okay.
I just want to talk.

20:59.910 --> 21:01.042
- I've said everything
I have to say to you.

21:01.129 --> 21:03.218
- No, that's fine.
Then just listen to this lady.

21:03.305 --> 21:04.524
- Who the hell is she?

21:04.611 --> 21:05.699
- She's a psychiatrist,
all right?

21:05.786 --> 21:08.745
She's gonna explain why
you should take me back.

21:08.832 --> 21:10.834
- Chloe, go back to your room.

21:10.921 --> 21:12.401
Yeah.

21:12.488 --> 21:14.055
[phone rings]

21:14.142 --> 21:15.709
- You called the cops?

21:15.796 --> 21:18.015
Why?
- Why do you think?

21:18.102 --> 21:20.148
You're not just a pervert,
you're a murderer, now?

21:20.235 --> 21:23.020
- I just needed his truck.
He came at me with a tire iron!

21:23.107 --> 21:25.022
He was gonna bash
my brains in.

21:25.109 --> 21:26.372
- I wish he would have.
- You don't mean that, Rosie.

21:26.459 --> 21:28.461
- I do.
- Hey. Hey!

21:28.548 --> 21:29.723
[gunshot]
- Aah!

21:29.810 --> 21:31.115
- Chloe, run!
That's my daughter, you--

21:31.202 --> 21:32.247
- I didn't see her!
- You animal!

21:32.334 --> 21:33.509
- No, I--
- How dare you?

21:33.596 --> 21:34.858
- I'm doing this
for our family!

21:34.945 --> 21:36.425
- You are not my family!
- Calm down!

21:36.512 --> 21:38.558
Shut up. Shut up!

21:38.645 --> 21:40.255
Here, come with me.
- No--no--

21:40.342 --> 21:42.431
- You're coming--
you're coming with me!

21:49.438 --> 21:51.571
[indistinct radio chatter]

21:51.658 --> 21:53.442
[distant sirens]

21:58.621 --> 21:59.927
- Gaines and Hana,
clear the house.

22:00.014 --> 22:01.885
Ray, check the yard.

22:01.972 --> 22:03.104
Dr. Kramer, you okay?

22:03.191 --> 22:04.627
- Noah Tramble did this.

22:04.714 --> 22:07.413
He has a gun, and he's
got Rose Franklin.

22:07.500 --> 22:08.892
- I want my mommy.
- You're safe now, OK?

22:08.979 --> 22:10.285
- Did you see where they went?
- Thank you.

22:10.372 --> 22:11.591
- I couldn't risk
looking back.

22:11.678 --> 22:12.940
I was trying to save Chloe
and myself.

22:13.027 --> 22:14.768
- Hey, Remy.
We got footprints.

22:14.855 --> 22:16.291
- Good job.

22:19.294 --> 22:21.905
[tense music]

22:21.992 --> 22:23.472
Another print.

22:27.215 --> 22:29.522
- Help! Help!

22:29.609 --> 22:32.873
He went that way,
towards the road.

22:32.960 --> 22:35.441
- Call Hana.

22:35.528 --> 22:37.181
Get with the state police,
and find this lunatic.

22:37.268 --> 22:39.140
- My daughter.
Is she okay?

22:39.227 --> 22:41.534
- She's fine.
We have her.

22:41.621 --> 22:43.449
- I thought
he was gonna kill me.

22:47.453 --> 22:48.541
Look.

22:48.628 --> 22:51.848
I'm a nurse,
and I'm all for therapy.

22:51.935 --> 22:54.416
And I ignored the journals
that Noah was keeping,

22:54.503 --> 22:56.940
until he left one out on
the kitchen counter one day

22:57.027 --> 22:59.639
when he thought I was at work.

22:59.726 --> 23:01.771
And I-I couldn't help it.
I read it.

23:01.858 --> 23:04.295
- What did you find?

23:04.383 --> 23:07.298
- Sick stuff...
about his half-sister

23:07.386 --> 23:09.910
and his pervert dad.

23:09.997 --> 23:12.695
He actually wrote in there,
"Am I my father?"

23:12.782 --> 23:15.829
And...I didn't know
anything about Casper.

23:15.916 --> 23:16.960
But when I looked him up
and saw that he was

23:17.047 --> 23:20.660
a sex offender who was
actually in prison, I...

23:20.747 --> 23:22.357
I kicked Noah out.

23:22.444 --> 23:26.187
And I told him to stay away
from Chloe and me, forever.

23:26.274 --> 23:28.407
- That's a hell of a trigger.

23:28.494 --> 23:30.409
- Yeah, that's what we thought.

23:30.496 --> 23:31.801
- Did Noah mention
anything today?

23:31.888 --> 23:34.630
The journals?
Rose kicking him out?

23:34.717 --> 23:36.284
- No.

23:36.371 --> 23:37.894
He was just obsessed with
finding out

23:37.981 --> 23:40.680
whether I thought
he molested Ruthie or not.

23:40.767 --> 23:42.246
- What'd you tell him?

23:42.333 --> 23:44.031
- Whatever I needed to
in the moment.

23:44.118 --> 23:45.815
I was scared.

23:45.902 --> 23:48.078
I was--I was just
trying to mollify him.

23:48.165 --> 23:49.558
- Did Ruthie ever
tell you directly

23:49.645 --> 23:51.081
that Noah molested her?
- No.

23:51.168 --> 23:54.650
I'm a mandated reporter.
I would have contacted police.

23:54.737 --> 23:56.435
- So how is it possible
that neither one of them

23:56.522 --> 23:58.872
knows exactly what happened?

23:58.959 --> 24:01.744
- Trauma is a tangled web.

24:01.831 --> 24:03.442
Ruthie was sleeping
when it happened.

24:03.529 --> 24:05.356
She thought she was dreaming.

24:05.444 --> 24:06.532
And she was young.

24:06.619 --> 24:08.316
She didn't have the words yet

24:08.403 --> 24:09.752
to describe
what was done to her.

24:09.839 --> 24:11.362
- What's Noah's excuse?

24:11.450 --> 24:13.756
- He was too drunk
and high to remember.

24:13.843 --> 24:16.455
But the people that
he trusted told him

24:16.542 --> 24:17.891
that he'd done something awful,

24:17.978 --> 24:20.763
so it's no wonder
he began to believe it.

24:20.850 --> 24:22.461
And Ruthie, too.

24:22.548 --> 24:24.767
- Like the McMartin
preschool case.

24:24.854 --> 24:26.856
Adults leading children
until they all started

24:26.943 --> 24:27.944
telling the same story.

24:28.031 --> 24:29.511
- That's one example.

24:29.598 --> 24:30.469
- I'll ask her about
it in the morning,

24:30.556 --> 24:32.209
when she's out of sedation.

24:32.296 --> 24:33.863
- What do you mean?

24:33.950 --> 24:35.865
- She attempted
suicide this morning.

24:35.952 --> 24:37.345
- [gasps]

24:41.218 --> 24:44.395
The unresolved trauma
of both Noah and Ruthie

24:44.483 --> 24:45.571
has manifested in violence.

24:45.658 --> 24:48.138
Noah has directed
his externally,

24:48.225 --> 24:50.358
and Ruthie has turned
hers against herself.

24:50.445 --> 24:53.230
- So, professional opinion.

24:53.317 --> 24:56.451
Did Noah molest Ruthie or not?

24:58.627 --> 25:00.150
- After what
I've been through today,

25:00.237 --> 25:03.980
and knowing about
his father now,

25:04.067 --> 25:05.634
I think he's guilty as hell.

25:16.645 --> 25:18.647
- Is now a good time?
- Yeah.

25:18.734 --> 25:20.562
I'm gonna be right
over here, okay?

25:22.433 --> 25:24.348
- Hey, Ruthie.
I'm Kristin.

25:24.435 --> 25:26.568
- My mom says you're nice.

25:26.655 --> 25:27.961
- Yeah?

25:28.048 --> 25:31.660
Gosh, I don't know if
my daughter would agree.

25:31.747 --> 25:33.444
She's a little mad
at me right now.

25:33.532 --> 25:36.622
How are you feeling?

25:36.709 --> 25:39.625
- I had nightmares all night.

25:39.712 --> 25:43.019
They say that kind
of thing is common, 'cause...

25:43.106 --> 25:44.368
I guess I'm trying to process
things that I didn't

25:44.455 --> 25:47.110
have the words to before.

25:47.197 --> 25:49.765
- I understand.

25:51.201 --> 25:52.638
- You do?

25:54.291 --> 25:55.641
- I do.

25:59.035 --> 26:02.082
Can you tell me what happened
that night, with Noah?

26:02.169 --> 26:04.867
- I wish I knew.

26:04.954 --> 26:06.826
I thought I was dreaming.

26:06.913 --> 26:08.392
And he only came to me
on nights

26:08.479 --> 26:10.525
when I was already asleep.

26:12.962 --> 26:14.573
- So it happened
more than once?

26:14.660 --> 26:16.662
- Yes.

26:16.749 --> 26:19.578
He never let me see his face.

26:19.665 --> 26:22.058
And I didn't
recognize his voice,

26:22.145 --> 26:23.973
because he always whispered.

26:24.060 --> 26:26.541
I asked him if I could
tell someone,

26:26.628 --> 26:28.456
and he said if I did that,

26:28.543 --> 26:31.154
he'd make sure
I never felt joy again.

26:33.156 --> 26:36.159
- And that's why you didn't
tell your mom or Dr. Kramer.

26:36.246 --> 26:37.726
- It's my fault Noah took her.

26:39.423 --> 26:41.164
I sent him to her.

26:41.251 --> 26:42.905
But only because I thought
she could help him,

26:42.992 --> 26:45.386
like she did me.

26:45.473 --> 26:47.127
It was so stupid of me.

26:47.214 --> 26:48.737
I mean, I could have
gotten her killed.

26:53.089 --> 26:58.312
My whole life, people have been
telling me I'm damaged goods.

26:58.399 --> 27:00.706
My own brother's victim.

27:00.793 --> 27:03.143
I get so tired of hearing it.

27:05.536 --> 27:08.235
And then sometimes
it goes away.

27:11.455 --> 27:14.154
But then I guess seeing Noah--

27:16.112 --> 27:18.898
Just...I'm just so ashamed.

27:22.989 --> 27:25.078
- Ruthie, I want you
to listen to me.

27:25.165 --> 27:27.776
You are not damaged goods.

27:27.863 --> 27:30.561
What you are is a survivor,
and that takes guts,

27:30.649 --> 27:32.259
and it takes courage.

27:32.346 --> 27:34.304
Real courage.

27:37.264 --> 27:41.572
And this is gonna sound
kind of crazy right now...

27:41.660 --> 27:43.574
you're going to be okay.

27:43.662 --> 27:46.403
You're way stronger
than you think.

27:48.144 --> 27:50.407
I see it.

27:52.627 --> 27:54.847
- I feel like I can
tell you anything.

27:56.370 --> 27:58.764
- And I'm so grateful you did.

28:04.073 --> 28:06.554
- Uh, the nurse said
it's time to go.

28:06.641 --> 28:08.512
They're transferring
her to a hospital

28:08.599 --> 28:09.557
where there's a
specialist who can

28:09.644 --> 28:11.298
do microsurgery on her wrists.

28:11.385 --> 28:13.517
- Can you come with us?

28:13.604 --> 28:16.042
- Yeah, of course.

28:16.129 --> 28:17.870
Yeah.

29:06.396 --> 29:07.571
- You okay?

29:08.834 --> 29:09.748
- [gasps]

29:14.970 --> 29:16.972
- Oh!

29:17.059 --> 29:17.973
- Oh my God!

29:18.060 --> 29:19.975
- [grunting]

29:20.062 --> 29:21.020
- Hey!
- What's going on?

29:21.107 --> 29:22.717
- I don't know.
What's happening?

29:22.804 --> 29:24.327
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.

29:27.243 --> 29:28.984
Noah, I'm with the FBI.

29:29.071 --> 29:31.378
I'm going to need you
to slow down.

29:31.465 --> 29:33.423
- It's okay. I'm here.

29:40.996 --> 29:44.565
[car horn honking]

29:44.652 --> 29:46.523
- Put your belt on.
- Okay.

29:51.180 --> 29:54.053
[sirens blaring]

30:02.452 --> 30:05.064
- Hey, it's him.
It's Noah.

30:05.151 --> 30:06.239
We're trapped in the back.

30:06.326 --> 30:07.153
- Can you tell
where he's headed?

30:07.240 --> 30:08.850
- Hold on.

30:08.937 --> 30:10.983
Take this.
- Okay.

30:13.507 --> 30:16.553
- Um...heading north
on Potomac Street.

30:16.640 --> 30:19.252
- Hana's tracking you, and
Hagerstown PD is en route.

30:19.339 --> 30:21.689
Kristin, do you have a shot?

30:21.776 --> 30:22.908
- The glass is thick.

30:22.995 --> 30:24.648
The round could ricochet.

30:24.735 --> 30:26.563
Even if I hit him,
he crashes this thing.

30:26.650 --> 30:29.088
Noah, stop the vehicle, now!

30:32.482 --> 30:35.007
[car horn honking]

30:39.707 --> 30:41.056
- He just ran
the light at 16th.

30:45.887 --> 30:47.236
[car horn honking]

30:47.323 --> 30:49.282
- Hang tight.
PD should be closing in.

30:49.369 --> 30:50.326
Stay on the phone with me.

30:50.413 --> 30:51.588
- Okay.

30:51.675 --> 30:54.678
[sirens blaring]

31:09.345 --> 31:10.912
- Kristin, what was that?

31:10.999 --> 31:13.045
Kristin, you with me?

31:13.132 --> 31:14.742
Gaines!

31:29.104 --> 31:30.758
You okay?

31:30.845 --> 31:33.108
- Noah took Ruthie.
- He took my baby girl.

31:33.195 --> 31:35.719
- Where'd they go?

31:35.806 --> 31:37.330
- No, no, no.
Kristin, Kristin.

31:37.417 --> 31:39.462
You need to get checked out.
Easy.

31:39.549 --> 31:42.901
- I should have taken the shot.
I should have taken the shot!

31:42.988 --> 31:45.381
- You did all you could do.
Just take it easy.

31:45.468 --> 31:47.557
Ray's on it.
Come on, sit down.

31:47.644 --> 31:49.472
- We need another ambulance.
- For who?

31:49.559 --> 31:51.300
- Your fugitive--he carjacked
a lady in a blue Dodge.

31:51.387 --> 31:52.171
Took off west.
- All right, look,

31:52.258 --> 31:54.129
alert your precinct.
Set a perimeter.

31:54.216 --> 31:55.957
Get a BOLO out on your
radio, all right? Let's go.

31:56.044 --> 31:58.046
- Listen to me.
Ruthie said at the hospital

31:58.133 --> 31:59.874
that she was abused
more than once.

32:01.920 --> 32:03.443
That means if it
happened on other nights,

32:03.530 --> 32:05.053
that means her father could
have been in the house.

32:05.140 --> 32:06.185
- Yeah, but Hana
checked his alibi.

32:06.272 --> 32:07.360
- We have to check again.

32:07.447 --> 32:09.536
Please.

32:11.059 --> 32:12.495
- I'll call her.

32:12.582 --> 32:14.628
Good work.

32:14.715 --> 32:16.412
- It's not good work.

32:16.499 --> 32:18.719
She would be--

32:18.806 --> 32:22.723
Ruthie would be here if
I did good work, wouldn't she?

32:25.378 --> 32:27.946
- I don't want to hurt you.
I never did.

32:28.033 --> 32:29.512
- Ten years.

32:29.599 --> 32:30.949
I spent so many nights

32:31.036 --> 32:33.603
wondering
what you were really like.

32:33.690 --> 32:36.128
Not the stories
everyone told me.

32:36.215 --> 32:38.130
But you never came to see me.

32:38.217 --> 32:40.088
- Mom and Luke wouldn't let me.

32:45.441 --> 32:48.053
I'm sorry, Ruthie.

32:48.140 --> 32:50.098
I wish I could
have seen you, too.

32:50.185 --> 32:52.753
- What do you want with me now?

32:52.840 --> 32:54.842
- To help you.

32:59.978 --> 33:02.806
I-I know this is hard.
- "I know this is hard."

33:04.634 --> 33:08.160
Does everyone start every
sentence to you that way, too?

33:08.247 --> 33:10.118
- [chuckles]

33:10.205 --> 33:11.946
Yeah.

33:12.033 --> 33:14.035
But I'm the villain.

33:16.037 --> 33:18.039
- I'm the victim.

33:22.826 --> 33:26.221
- Look, I don't remember
anything about that night

33:26.308 --> 33:28.876
except waking up in a fog
and Mom yelling at me

33:28.963 --> 33:30.747
and then calling Luke
to come home.

33:34.577 --> 33:36.971
- I've been having nightmares.

33:38.059 --> 33:40.279
And I-I think...

33:40.366 --> 33:44.065
I think
they're helping me remember.

33:44.152 --> 33:45.806
Like, those nights I--

33:45.893 --> 33:47.025
- W-wait.

33:47.112 --> 33:48.635
Nights?

33:49.853 --> 33:52.595
What do you mean, nights?

33:52.682 --> 33:54.554
There was only one night.

33:54.641 --> 33:56.817
March 1, 2013.

33:56.904 --> 33:58.471
- No.

33:58.558 --> 34:00.777
No, Noah,
that wasn't the only night.

34:00.864 --> 34:04.303
There were others,
after that night.

34:04.390 --> 34:07.088
- Other--other nights?
What--

34:07.175 --> 34:09.569
After I was
kicked out of the house?

34:17.403 --> 34:20.362
- I'm so sorry, Noah.

34:20.449 --> 34:23.365
I let them tell me stories
about what happened to me,

34:23.452 --> 34:26.194
and I started to
believe the stories.

34:26.281 --> 34:28.849
But I--I knew--

34:28.936 --> 34:30.372
I ruined your life.

34:35.421 --> 34:38.250
Noah, you didn't do this.

34:41.253 --> 34:44.560
- Ruthie...who did?

34:47.650 --> 34:49.652
- Hey.

34:49.739 --> 34:51.915
Blue Dodge was spotted exiting
the Beltway in Virginia.

34:52.002 --> 34:53.134
They're headed
towards Falls Church.

34:54.831 --> 34:56.659
- Why the hell would Noah
take Ruthie to Virginia?

34:56.746 --> 34:59.140
- My ex.

34:59.227 --> 35:00.794
Luke Denham.
He remarried a few years ago.

35:00.881 --> 35:02.274
They just moved there
with their daughter.

35:02.361 --> 35:03.579
- How old is their daughter?

35:03.666 --> 35:07.061
- Three, I think.

35:07.148 --> 35:10.020
- It could be Luke
is Noah's next target.

35:10.108 --> 35:11.761
I just circled back
on his alibi.

35:11.848 --> 35:14.503
Now, he was in trial in
Baltimore in March 2013.

35:14.590 --> 35:17.115
But on the morning of March 1,
his particular proceeding

35:17.202 --> 35:18.377
was marked continued
till the afternoon session,

35:18.464 --> 35:20.248
as per the court docket.

35:20.335 --> 35:23.208
Because Luke was driving from
Hagerstown back to Baltimore.

35:23.295 --> 35:24.861
- What?
How can that be?

35:24.948 --> 35:26.776
How can you know that?
That was ten years ago.

35:26.863 --> 35:28.604
- They had credit card
receipts then, too.

35:28.691 --> 35:31.955
Your ex-husband was buying gas
Outside Hagerstown At 5:53 a.m.

35:32.042 --> 35:33.218
- He drove from Hagerstown
to Baltimore and back

35:33.305 --> 35:34.828
in the middle of the night,

35:34.915 --> 35:36.743
the same night that you found
Noah in Ruthie's bed.

35:36.830 --> 35:38.136
You have an address on Luke?

35:38.223 --> 35:39.789
- Yeah. Bennett Road.

35:39.876 --> 35:41.400
- Send it to everyone,
and alert SWAT and PD.

35:41.487 --> 35:42.923
We need to get to
Falls Church, now.

35:43.010 --> 35:44.359
Let's go get her.

35:54.064 --> 35:55.936
[sighs loudly]

35:57.503 --> 35:58.634
- Noah?

36:01.202 --> 36:03.335
Ruthie.

36:03.422 --> 36:06.642
[dark music]

36:13.040 --> 36:16.565
[dramatic music]

36:16.652 --> 36:22.223
♪ ♪

36:34.322 --> 36:35.454
- You don't want to do this!

36:35.541 --> 36:36.585
- Upstairs.

36:39.501 --> 36:41.895
- You want to hurt me?

36:41.982 --> 36:43.201
Come on!

36:43.288 --> 36:46.073
You don't want to do this!

36:46.160 --> 36:47.683
- [whispering] Hey, Ruthie.

36:47.770 --> 36:49.207
- Put it down.
- Is Noah in there?

36:49.294 --> 36:50.556
- Yeah.
- Okay.

36:50.643 --> 36:53.820
- Look at me.

36:53.907 --> 36:55.430
Noah!
I am not the bad guy here.

36:55.517 --> 36:57.954
- [whispering]
Take her downstairs.

36:58.041 --> 36:59.434
- Put that down!

36:59.521 --> 37:01.306
- I got you, Ruthie.
Just keep breathing, okay?

37:01.393 --> 37:03.873
Come on.
Nice and slow.

37:03.960 --> 37:06.136
- Stop, Noah, you don't
have to do this, please!

37:06.224 --> 37:08.530
Stop, Noah--
- FBI!

37:08.617 --> 37:10.140
Drop your weapon!
- He admitted it.

37:10.228 --> 37:11.620
He admitted everything.

37:11.707 --> 37:13.361
He molested Ruthie.

37:13.448 --> 37:17.235
When she threatened to talk,
he drugged me with my own oxy

37:17.322 --> 37:18.410
and put me in her bed.

37:18.497 --> 37:21.326
He used me as a scapegoat.

37:21.413 --> 37:23.066
Because what did
my life matter, anyway?

37:23.153 --> 37:25.286
And what did Ruthie's?

37:25.373 --> 37:27.332
I'm gonna make sure

37:27.419 --> 37:29.029
he never hurts
another little girl again.

37:29.116 --> 37:30.422
- Please, I'm sorry.

37:30.509 --> 37:32.075
I said-I said I'm sorry.
Please.

37:32.162 --> 37:34.774
- Is that the whisper you
used when you molested Ruthie?

37:34.861 --> 37:35.992
Is that what you're gonna do
to your new daughter

37:36.079 --> 37:36.993
when she's grown up?

37:37.080 --> 37:38.473
- No!
- Oh, no.

37:38.560 --> 37:39.866
Probably going to
have to wait until she

37:39.953 --> 37:40.910
gets out of diapers, right?

37:40.997 --> 37:42.042
Right?

37:42.129 --> 37:43.304
- Hey, Noah.

37:45.088 --> 37:47.177
Listen to me.

37:47.265 --> 37:48.483
Your whole life,
you've been in--

37:48.570 --> 37:50.224
- No!
Don't psychoanalyze me!

37:50.311 --> 37:52.574
I was telling the truth

37:52.661 --> 37:55.055
when I said
I passed out that night.

37:55.142 --> 37:56.970
He's the one who snuck into
Ruthie's room and hurt her,

37:57.057 --> 37:58.450
not me.

37:58.537 --> 38:00.495
- Yeah, and he
hurt you too, Noah.

38:01.844 --> 38:03.063
- [grunts]

38:04.586 --> 38:06.022
- Didn't he?

38:08.503 --> 38:11.680
And you're right.
I'm not a psychiatrist, okay?

38:11.767 --> 38:13.378
I'm just a human
being who knows

38:13.465 --> 38:15.728
that you didn't hurt Ruthie.

38:15.815 --> 38:19.166
And you probably didn't mean
to hurt anybody else.

38:19.253 --> 38:22.648
You just wanted
the truth, right?

38:25.172 --> 38:27.566
And now you have it, okay?

38:27.653 --> 38:28.654
We all know.

38:31.221 --> 38:33.311
Hey, Noah.
Please look at me.

38:36.009 --> 38:38.316
Noah, look at me.

38:41.841 --> 38:45.540
You are just as much a victim
in this as your sister is.

38:47.237 --> 38:48.848
So please don't
make this worse.

38:48.935 --> 38:51.241
Show us who you are.

38:52.678 --> 38:54.027
Let him go.

38:54.114 --> 38:56.029
[whispering] Let him go.

38:56.116 --> 38:58.161
- [sobbing]

39:00.033 --> 39:03.079
[music intensifies]

39:03.166 --> 39:07.867
♪ ♪

39:07.954 --> 39:10.652
[weeping]

39:10.739 --> 39:13.089
- Oh, thank God.

39:13.176 --> 39:14.569
Thank God, thank God.

39:18.225 --> 39:19.792
- Hands behind your back.

39:19.879 --> 39:22.360
- Where you're going,
what you did--

39:22.447 --> 39:25.145
you're going to
wish he killed you.

39:26.320 --> 39:28.540
- [sobbing]

39:36.983 --> 39:38.593
[door opens]

39:47.994 --> 39:49.517
- Hey.

39:54.261 --> 39:55.958
How was your day?

39:56.045 --> 39:57.438
- Fine.

40:02.400 --> 40:04.227
- Pictures from the party?

40:04.314 --> 40:05.577
- I didn't go, Mom.

40:05.664 --> 40:08.188
- Yeah, I know you didn't.

40:08.275 --> 40:09.668
Thank you.

40:11.757 --> 40:13.019
You wanna put that down
for a second?

40:13.106 --> 40:14.760
I wanna talk to you.

40:20.722 --> 40:23.551
- What happened to your head?

40:23.638 --> 40:24.683
- Mm.

40:24.770 --> 40:25.988
Looks worse than it is.
I'm fine.

40:26.075 --> 40:27.686
- Happened at work?

40:29.296 --> 40:31.298
Wait, I forgot.

40:31.385 --> 40:32.430
We don't talk about that.

40:35.345 --> 40:37.913
- There's a reason, Ingrid.

40:38.000 --> 40:41.090
It's not because I'm
trying to hide anything

40:41.177 --> 40:42.614
or because I don't trust you.

40:42.701 --> 40:44.224
It's because I want
to protect you.

40:45.443 --> 40:47.357
- From what?

40:47.445 --> 40:49.011
- I don't want you
to worry about me.

40:49.098 --> 40:51.361
- Mom, I--

40:51.449 --> 40:52.841
I know what your job is,

40:52.928 --> 40:54.582
and I know
that it's dangerous.

40:54.669 --> 40:55.627
I'm...

40:58.586 --> 41:01.546
I'm really proud
of what you do.

41:04.200 --> 41:06.507
- Thanks, kid.

41:09.075 --> 41:11.381
- Can you at least
promise me one thing?

41:11.469 --> 41:12.644
- [clears throat]

41:12.731 --> 41:14.036
I can.

41:14.123 --> 41:18.780
- If you're ever not okay,
you'll tell me.

41:18.867 --> 41:21.261
- I will.

41:21.348 --> 41:22.654
- Because you can't protect
me forever, you know.

41:22.741 --> 41:25.874
- I don't know about that.

41:25.961 --> 41:27.049
Don't count on it.

41:27.136 --> 41:28.877
- I'm serious.

41:28.964 --> 41:32.446
In six months,
I will be in college.

41:32.533 --> 41:36.232
Drinking beer, doing drugs.

41:36.319 --> 41:38.365
- Ugh.
- Having sex.

41:38.452 --> 41:41.716
I might even fall in love.

41:41.803 --> 41:43.588
- Well, that is usually
the order of things.

41:44.806 --> 41:47.069
- Did you just make a joke?

41:47.156 --> 41:49.594
- I think I did.

41:49.681 --> 41:51.857
- How hard did you
get hit in the head?

41:51.944 --> 41:55.034
- Really hard, because I'm
thinking about cooking dinner.

41:55.121 --> 41:57.558
- Oh, no.

41:57.645 --> 41:59.255
- Bad idea.
Just kidding.

41:59.342 --> 42:02.737
Pizza, Thai, or Chinese?

42:02.824 --> 42:04.173
- Chinese.

42:04.260 --> 42:06.524
- Yeah, I knew you
were gonna say Chinese.

42:08.917 --> 42:11.267
- Mmm.

42:11.354 --> 42:13.443
Ooh, that one's really good.

42:13.531 --> 42:16.446
- I love that one.
- Mm-hmm.

42:16.534 --> 42:19.362
[soft, somber music]

42:43.952 --> 42:45.084
[wolf howls]
